The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Frontpage | Old-aged woman mauled by bear
                                                                                                           Old-aged woman mauled by bear
          STAFF REPORTER                              
	New Delhi, Jul 27 (PTI) A 70-year-old woman was mauled by a bear at Beharda village in Rajasthans Kelodavi Sanctuary, forcing the villagers to move out of the protected area (PA) as per government suggestion.              
	 quot;Earlier, only a few out of the 60 families in the village were ready to accept the compensation package to make the area inviolate. But now after the incident which happened four days back, the entire village has agreed to move out, quot; R P Gupta, Deputy Conservator of Forest, Karoli division told PTI.              
	 quot;As per the Central governments package, the villagers are being offered Rs 10 lakh per family or a piece of land. We are working out the deal with them, quot; he added.              
	Gupta said the victim Sugali was mauled by a black bear in the sanctuary which is part of the Ranthambore Tiger Reserve, an habitat of around 40 tigers.                                                                                                                                             
